comments: Bridges (PHX) does not step out of bounds when he saves the ball back into play.
Ayton (PHX) establishes himself in LeVert's (CLE) path and does not deliver illegal contact during the pick.
Allen (CLE) legally contests Shamet's (PHX) driving shot attempt.
Ayton (PHX) and Mobley (CLE) briefly engage and disengage as they pursue the rebound.
Ayton (PHX) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.
Paul (PHX) is moving alongside LeVert's (CLE) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Allen (CLE) makes contact with the ball prior to the ensuing arm contact with Ayton (PHX), which is marginal.
Ayton (PHX) raises his hand up into Mitchell's (CLE) arm and initiates contact that affects Mitchell's shot near the rim.
Allen (CLE) brings his arm down and initiates contact with Bridges' (PHX) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Ayton (PHX) makes contact with Allen's (CLE) arm that affects his ability to secure the rebound.
Shamet (PHX) legally contests Mitchell's (CLE) jump shot attempt.
Mobley (CLE) and Bridges (PHX) come together at the same spot and marginal contact occurs off ball.
LeVert (CLE) and Shamet (PHX) engage and disengage and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Ayton (PHX) establishes himself in LeVert's (CLE) path and does not deliver illegal contact during the screen.
Allen (CLE) legally contests Shamet's (PHX) jump shot attempt.
Shamet (PHX) is moving alongside Mitchell's (CLE) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Mitchell (CLE) briefly grasps and immediately releases Bridges' (PHX) uniform as marginal contact occurs during the inbound.
Mitchell (CLE) legally contests Bridges' (PHX) jump shot attempt.
Allen (CLE) and Ayton (PHX) briefly engage and disengage during rebounding.
